==English==

===Etymology===
Derived from the Germanic word ''Walha'', meaning "foreigner," probably derived from the term ''[[Volcae]]''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK|US}} {{enPR|wālz}}, {{IPA|/weɪlz/}}, {{SAMPA|/weIlz/}}
* {{audio|en-us-Wales.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|eɪlz}}
* Homophones: [[wail]]s (''in accents with the [[wine-whine merger]]''), [[whale]]s (''in accents with the wine-whine merger'')

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# A [[principality]] in the west of, and one of the constituent [[nation]]s of, the [[United Kingdom]].

